    "file_path": "h2q_project/Dockerfile",
    "content": "FROM ubuntu:latest

# Install dependencies
RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
    build-essential \
    cmake \
    git \
    python3 \
    python3-pip \
    wget \
    unzip \
    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

# Install ONNX Runtime
RUN pip3 install onnxruntime

# Set working directory
WORKDIR /app

# Copy source code
COPY . .

# Build the H2Q geometry kernel
RUN mkdir build && cd build && cmake .. && make

# Add a simple test to verify ONNX Runtime acceleration (example)
RUN echo "import onnxruntime; print('ONNX Runtime version:', onnxruntime.__version__)" > test_onnx.py

# Command to run the test (customize this to run an H2Q kernel example with ONNX)
CMD ["python3", "test_onnx.py"]"
